dc_description_s: This polygon layer contains parcels with preservation easements or that have been designated as landmarks by the Cambridge City Council. It also contains parcels with Massachusetts Historical Commission (MHC) easements. A landmark is a place, structure, feature, or object that has been designated by the City Council as historically or architecturally significant by itself or because it is associated with events, persons, or trends significant to the history of the City of Cambridge.
dc_publisher_s: Cambridge (MA) Geographic Information System (City of Cambridge GIS)
